<p>The <code>decrement</code> tag decrements a variable by 1.</p>

<h2>Basic Decrement</h2>
<pre>{open}set counter=10{close}
Before: {open}$counter{close}
{open}decrement $counter{close}
After: {open}$counter{close}</pre>
{set counter=10}
<p>Before: {$counter}</p>
{decrement $counter}
<p>After: {$counter}</p>

<h2>Multiple Decrements</h2>
<pre>{open}set n=5{close}
{open}decrement $n{close} n = {open}$n{close}
{open}decrement $n{close} n = {open}$n{close}
{open}decrement $n{close} n = {open}$n{close}</pre>
{set n=5}
<p>{decrement $n}n = {$n}</p>
<p>{decrement $n}n = {$n}</p>
<p>{decrement $n}n = {$n}</p>

<h2>Countdown Loop</h2>
<pre>{open}set i=5{close}
{open}while $i > 0{close}
  {open}$i{close}...
  {open}decrement $i{close}
{open}/while{close}
Liftoff!</pre>
{set i=5}
<p>
{while $i > 0}
  {$i}...
  {decrement $i}
{/while}
Liftoff!</p>

<h2>Decrement Creates Variable</h2>
<pre>{open}decrement $newCounter{close}
Value: {open}$newCounter{close}</pre>
<p>Decrementing undefined variable creates it with value -1:</p>
{decrement $newCounter}
<p>Value: {$newCounter}</p>

<h2>Countdown from PHP Variable</h2>
<pre>PHP set $countdown = 5
{open}while $countdown > 0{close}
  {open}$countdown{close}
  {open}decrement $countdown{close}
{open}/while{close}</pre>
<p>Countdown:
{while $countdown > 0}{$countdown} {decrement $countdown}{/while}Done!</p>

<h2>Increment vs Decrement</h2>
<pre>{open}set x=5{close}
{open}increment $x{close} = {open}$x{close} (was 5)
{open}decrement $x{close} = {open}$x{close} (back to 5)
{open}decrement $x{close} = {open}$x{close} (now 4)</pre>
{set x=5}
<p>Start: x = {$x}</p>
<p>{increment $x}After increment: x = {$x}</p>
<p>{decrement $x}After decrement: x = {$x}</p>
<p>{decrement $x}After another decrement: x = {$x}</p>
